datasets when compared against the passive, microwave-based (MW), monthly
mean LWP data of <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="bib1.bibx33" id="normal.51"/> in the period 2003 to 2008. The
validation was performed for three oceanic stratocumulus regions for which
the frequency of ice cloud occurrence is very small: SAF, west of Africa
(10ג€“20<inline-formula><mml:math id="M256" display="inline"><mml:msup><mml:mi/><mml:mo>גˆ˜</mml:mo></mml:msup></mml:math></inline-formula>ג€¯S, 0ג€“10<inline-formula><mml:math id="M257" display="inline"><mml:msup><mml:mi/><mml:mo>גˆ˜</mml:mo></mml:msup></mml:math></inline-formula>ג€¯E); SAM, west of South America
(16ג€“26<inline-formula><mml:math id="M258" display="inline"><mml:msup><mml:mi/><mml:mo>גˆ˜</mml:mo></mml:msup></mml:math></inline-formula>ג€¯S, 76ג€“86<inline-formula><mml:math id="M259" display="inline"><mml:msup><mml:mi/><mml:mo>גˆ˜</mml:mo></mml:msup></mml:math></inline-formula>ג€¯W); NAM, west of California
